      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"purpose\" you're talking about feels like a coping mechanism, a way to distract ourselves from the reality of our insignificance. It doesn't actually change the fact that we're just biological accidents. All that \"connection\" and \"creativity\" is just something we do to avoid looking into the abyss. It feels exhausting to keep pretending it's worth the effort.",
